# GEO-Pulse Base Rules

## Project Context
GEO-Pulse is a freemium AI Search Readiness auditor built on:
- Next.js 15 App Router deployed via `@opennextjs/cloudflare` (NOT `@cloudflare/next-on-pages` — that package is deprecated)
- Cloudflare Workers for the scan engine, PDF generation, and webhook handling
- Supabase for database + auth (Row Level Security required on ALL tables)
- Gemini 2.5 Flash-Lite for semantic reasoning (2 calls only: Q&A detection + extractability)
- pdf-lib for PDF generation (NOT Puppeteer — cannot run in CF Worker V8 isolate)
- Stripe for payments (2.9% + $0.30 per transaction, no monthly fee)
- Resend for transactional email

## TypeScript
- Always use `strict: true` TypeScript
- No `any` types — use `unknown` and narrow with type guards
- Prefer explicit return types on all exported functions
- No `console.log` in production code — use structured logging only
- Use `satisfies` operator for config objects

## Code Style
- Prefer `const` over `let`; never use `var`
- Use named exports, not default exports (except Next.js page components)
- Keep functions small and single-purpose
- All async functions must have explicit error handling — never swallow errors silently
- Prefer early returns over nested conditionals

## Naming Conventions
- Files: kebab-case (`scan-engine.ts`, not `scanEngine.ts`)
- Components: PascalCase (`ScanForm.tsx`)
- Functions/variables: camelCase
- Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE
- Database tables: snake_case (matches Supabase convention)

## What Never To Do
- NEVER let the AI generate authentication logic from scratch — use Supabase Auth or Better Auth
- NEVER let the AI generate Stripe webhook handlers from scratch — copy from official Stripe docs
- NEVER hardcode secrets, API keys, or credentials in source code
- NEVER use `@cloudflare/next-on-pages` — it is deprecated, use `@opennextjs/cloudflare`
- NEVER suggest Vercel for hosting — commercial use is prohibited on the hobby plan
- NEVER suggest Make.com — 1,000 ops/month free tier is 15x too low for this workload
- NEVER use Puppeteer or Playwright in Workers — they cannot run in V8 isolates
- NEVER use Node.js built-ins in Workers code (`fs`, `path`, `crypto` from Node, etc.)

## Score Naming
The score is ALWAYS called "AI Search Readiness Score". Never use:
- "citation probability"
- "AI ranking score"
- "AI visibility score"
- Any phrasing that implies predicted outcomes
